If that doesn't help, please modify the demo I shared to demonstrate the issue being described.

I wonder if you are catching the editComplete as it is bubbling up from the `td` to the `table`?

It might be better to not use delegated events since you can't stop them from bubbling up the DOM tree. Instead, just bind to the "editComplete" event on the table and use the `event.target` to get the element. Something like this:

```js
$('table').on('editComplete', function(e){
    // the "editComplete event is triggered on the div within the cell
    var $this = $( e.target ).closest('td');
    /// do whatever
});

