Hi @biocar2001!

I don't use knockout, so I'm not very familiar with how it works. After reading the contents of the links you shared, I think I might know what is needed to fix this issue.

You didn't state this about knockout, but from looking at the Plunker in the answer on Stackoverflow, I see that the build widget is needed to process & build the table from the knockout array. The build widget was originally written to only work on initialization; but I think you can use it instead of calling "update" or "updateAll". *I haven't tried this method before*, but the following code looks like it should work:

```js
init: function(element, valueAccessor) {
    var iden=$(element).attr("id");
    if($(element).hasClass('tablesorter')){
        $.tablesorter.buildTable( element, element.config );
    }else{
        $(element).tablesorter({
            widgetOptions:{filter_external : '#'+iden+"_search"}
        }).tablesorterPager({container: $('#'+iden+"_pager")});
    }
},
```

This code assumes that `element` is the `table`. `element` could also be the wrapper, but then it would append a new table.

As I said, without the date range, the '{no one]' and '{nothing}' options all work as designed. So those objects are not in question...I hope. :) It's just the date range that is causing the setFilter function to fail.

Here are the relevant details:

1. I wanted to have the default state of the table to have no rows shown
2. I used filter_selectSource to add an '{all}' selection.
3. I added filter_functions to handle '{no one}', '{nothing}', and '{all}'.
4. I set the first option values in the filter select boxes to '{no one}' and '{nothing}', respectively in the filterInit event.
5. At the end of the filterInit handler I call setFilter to refresh the table filters.

Here is the relevant code:

so.widgetOptions.filter_selectSource = {
	".cnc-who" 		: 	function (table, column, onlyAvail) {
							var array = $.tablesorter.filter.getOptions(table, column, onlyAvail);
							array.splice( 1, 0, "{all}" );
							return array;
						},
	".cnc-class" 	: 	function (table, column, onlyAvail) {
							var array = $.tablesorter.filter.getOptions(table, column, onlyAvail);
							array.splice( 1, 0, "{all}" );
							return array;
						}
};
so.widgetOptions.filter_functions = {
	".cnc-who"		: 	{
							"{no one}" :	function (e, n, f, i, $r, c) {
												return false;
											},
							"{all}"		:	function (e, n, f, i, $r, c) {
												return true;
											}
						},
	".cnc-class"	: 	{
							"{nothing}"	:	function (e, n, f, i, $r, c) {
												return false;
											},
							"{all}"		:	function (e, n, f, i, $r, c) {
												return true;
											}
						}
};

