@andy-esch so I was just checking this page out (https://github.com/CartoDB/cartodb/blob/master/services/importer/lib/importer/overviews.rb)

And perhaps, thinking out loud a bit here, if you are importing files, and type-guessing is off and these are a-spatial tables (no defined geom) or non-point tables (https://github.com/CartoDB/cartodb/blob/master/services/importer/lib/importer/overviews.rb#L89), you should be not have Overviews triggered via the Importer. 

For more on overviews, I find this doc to be super useful; https://github.com/CartoDB/cartodb-postgresql/blob/master/doc/CDB_Overviews.md 

    SELECT CDB_CreateOverviews('table_name');
    SELECT CDB_DropOverviews('table_name');
    SELECT CDB_Overviews('table_name');

And @jgoizueta is very likely the most knowledgable person about Overviews.

