I've ended up just running Diamond with cgroup confinement on my systems to keep it from taking the whole system down when Graphite backs up.

cgconfig.conf:

    group diamond {
      memory {
        memory.limit_in_bytes = 128M;
      }
    }

I then updated the Upstart config (Ubuntu 14.04) to launch Diamond with:

        exec start-stop-daemon --start --make-pidfile --chuid $DIAMOND_USER --pidfile $DIAMOND_PID --exec /usr/bin/cgexec -- -g memory:diamond $DAEMON --foreground --skip-change-user --skip-fork --skip-pidfile

